      "content": "i guess. but it's just hard to find the \"appreciation\" in it. it feels like we're just trapped in this loop of wanting things and suffering when we can't have them, all for a system that's fundamentally broken and meaningless. if the whole thing is just a temporary accident of physics, then why is there such a massive pressure to keep enduring it? wouldn't it be more rational to just step out of the loop while you can?",
